      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>WM. WRIGLEY JR., Chicago, the chewing gum maker, said it had won United States clearance to buy the Life Savers and Altoids candy brands from Kraft Foods, Northfield, Ill., for $1.48 billion.</p>
        <p>ALCOA, Pittsburgh, the aluminum maker, said it would close a plant in Elyria, Ohio, which makes rigid plastic sheet for the company's Kama unit.</p>
